references: Keypoint localization is a position-sensitive vision task. To illustrate the effect of position embedding, we conduct experiments based on TokenPose-S-v111 with different position embedding types (i.e., no position embedding, 222D sine and learnable position embedding). As Table 7 shown, employing position embedding significantly improves the performance by 5.55.55.5 AP at most. In particular, 222D sine position embedding performs better than learnable position embedding, which is as expected since the 222D spatial information is required for predicting heatmaps.
